### ROOM LAYOUT BUILDER PAGE

Step-by-step flow:

STEP 1 — Guest house selector
Dropdown to select guest house. On select, show guest house name + city + number of floors.

STEP 2 — Floor tabs
Tabs: Floor 1, Floor 2, Floor 3 (dynamic based on floors count).

STEP 3 — Grid + room panel
Two-panel layout:
Left panel (65%): Visual 4×3 grid of cells.
- Empty cells: light dashed border, "+" icon in center, cursor pointer
- Placed room cells: colored card showing room number (bold) + type (small) + status dot
- Clicking empty cell → highlights it (blue border) + opens right panel form
- Clicking placed room → opens right panel with room details for edit/remove

Right panel (35%): "Place Room" form
- Room Number* (text, e.g. "101")
- Room Type* (radio: Single / Double / Suite)
- Amenities (checkboxes: AC, WiFi, TV, Kitchen, Geyser)
- "Place Room" primary button → places room card in selected cell
- If editing: "Update Room" + "Remove Room" (red, with confirm) buttons

Bottom bar: "Save Layout" primary button → console.log the full layout JSON + show success toast "Layout saved successfully"

Grid cell states:
- Empty: bg white, border dashed #cbd5e1, "+" text #94a3b8
- Selected empty: bg #eff6ff, border solid #3b82f6
- Placed (available): bg #E1F5EE, border #5DCAA5
- Placed (maintenance): bg #FCEBEB, border #F09595

