### ROOM GRID PAGE

Floor tabs at top (Floor 1, Floor 2, Floor 3).
Filter pills: All · Available · Booked · Occupied · Maintenance
Stat count badges next to each filter.

4-column CSS grid. Rooms positioned by grid_x and grid_y from layout.

Room card design:
- Room number (18px bold)
- Room type (12px muted)
- Status dot (top-right corner, 8px circle)
- Apply exact status colors from design system
- If Occupied: show guest name + "Out: [date]" below type
- If Booked: show guest name + "In: [date]" below type
- If Maintenance: show category below type in red muted text

Clicking any room card → opens RIGHT SIDE DRAWER (slides from right, 380px wide, overlay backdrop):

Drawer header: Room [number] · [type] · Floor [n]
Amenities row: small icon badges (AC, WiFi, TV etc.)
Current status badge (large, colored)

Drawer content by status:

IF AVAILABLE:
  Show "No active booking" message
  "Create Booking" green primary button → navigates to New Booking page with room pre-selected

IF BOOKED:
  Guest info card: name, phone, company
  Scheduled check-in: date + time
  Scheduled check-out: date + time
  Duration: X nights
  "Check In" green button → sets actual_checkin = now, status → Occupied, success toast
  "Cancel Booking" red outlined button → confirm modal → cancels booking, status → Available

IF OCCUPIED:
  Guest info card: name, phone, company
  Checked in at: actual timestamp
  Scheduled check-out: date + time
  "Check Out" amber button → confirm modal "Confirm checkout for [guest]?" → sets actual_checkout = now, status → Maintenance (for cleaning purposes - see note below), creates maintenance log, success toast
  "Report Issue" secondary outlined button → opens Report Issue modal

IF MAINTENANCE:
  Issue details: category badge, priority badge
  Description text
  Reported at timestamp
  Status: Open / In Progress
  "Mark In Progress" button (if Open)
  "Mark Resolved" button → opens resolution modal (resolution note required) → on resolve: status → Available, ticket closed

Note on Check Out: when manager clicks Check Out, room status goes to "Maintenance" temporarily for the cleaning buffer period (configurable, default 60 mins). After manager manually marks it ready via the Maintenance page, it becomes Available. This replaces the separate Housekeeping module.

