## IMPORTANT RULES

1. Remove ALL employee management — no employees page, no employee data, no employee-related fields anywhere.
2. Remove ALL separate housekeeping module — post-checkout cleaning is handled as a maintenance ticket type.
3. Room status flow: Available → Booked → Occupied → Maintenance (cleaning) → Available
4. Maintenance page is the single place to manage both real issues and post-checkout cleaning.
5. "Mark Room for Maintenance" is the primary way manager blocks a room — it creates a ticket AND blocks the room.
6. Room in Maintenance status = invisible in New Booking dropdown and Room Grid available filter.
7. All reports scoped to manager's guest house only.
8. Admin reports span all guest houses.
9. No approval workflow — manager creates bookings directly, no employee self-booking.
10. Guest has no login — manager enters guest info manually.
